---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Engagement Options | Links AI"
  description="Links AI can help with workflow assessment, build and launch, and ongoing support for practical AI systems."
  pageClass="page-services"
>
  <section class="hero" slot="hero">
    <h1>Engagement options</h1>
    <p>
      Most clients start in one of three places: figuring out where to begin,
      building the first system, or improving something that is already live.
    </p>
    <a class="btn" href="/contact">Get in touch</a>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Where clients usually start</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Assess the workflow</h3>
        <p>You know there is operational drag, but you want clarity on what to fix first and what is worth building.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Build the first system</h3>
        <p>You already know the process you want to improve and want help designing, implementing, and launching it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Support and improve</h3>
        <p>You want the system to stay useful after launch, with refinement, monitoring, and expansion over time.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>The simple version</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Not sure where to start?</h3>
        <p>We help identify the best first workflow.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Already know the workflow?</h3>
        <p>We build and launch the system.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Want ongoing help?</h3>
        <p>We keep improving what is already working.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-box">
    <h2>Need the fuller picture?</h2>
    <p>If you want to understand the customer journey end to end, visit the how it works page.</p>
    <a class="btn" href="/how-it-works">View how it works</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
